  <!--<h2 class="entrydate">
    October 9, 2009  </h2>  --> <h3 class="entrytitle" id="post-1869"> <a href="http://longorshortcapital.com/look-out-moon-dont-mess-around-with-gods-america.htm" rel="bookmark">
    Look Out Moon, Don&#8217;t Mess Around With God&#8217;s America    </a> </h3><small>by Johnny Debacle<br></small>
  <div class="entrybody">
    <blockquote><p>America will blow up the moon, we have the technology, the time is now, science can wait no longer, children are our future, America can, should, must, and WILL blow up the moon&#8230;And we&#8217;ll be doing it during a full moon so we make sure we get it all.</p></blockquote>
<p><small>Quote from <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Csj7vMKy4EI">Mr. Show</a> in 1996</small></p>
<p>I don&#8217;t mean to be that monkey, but why are we blowing up the moon?  Has it come to this?  I understand that this is a <a href="http://www.latimes.com/news/science/la-sciw-moon-hole9-2009oct09,0,1252219.story?track=rss" class="broken_link">search for water</a> but at $79 million, aren&#8217;t their cheaper local sources?  Isn&#8217;t this the kind of thing that leads to more global warming?  E.g. sourcing water from the moon and then shipping it here burns more fossil fuels than even bottled water, according to my model at least.</p>
<p><strong>Recommendation:</strong>  Short moon real estate.  While it&#8217;s likely to benefit from increased scarcity, it&#8217;s also likely to be negatively impacted by being exploded.</p>
	

